 his coat with his palm, donned his hat, and without looking back walked toward the house.

The elevator proved to be out of order but Luzhin made no complaint.

His thirst for movement was not yet slaked. He began to climb the stairs and since he lived a very long way up his ascent continued for some time; he seemed to be climbing a skyscraper. Finally he reached the last landing, took a deep breath, crunched the key in the lock and stepped into the entrance hall. His wife came from the study t